05/01/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK officials confirmed on Tuesday (4 January) that UN administrator Soren Jessen-Petersen and Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica will meet in Belgrade on 17 January. 
They are expected to discuss issues related to security, decentralisation and the protection of minorities. 
Belgrade's co-ordinator for Kosovo, Nebojsa Covic, added on Tuesday that Serbia would also insist on resolving the issue of power cuts in Serb-populated villages in Kosovo. 
(Danas - 05/01/05; KosovaLive, Tanjug - 04/01/05)
